                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18450512-name-1071" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-1071" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-1071" type="surname" value="CHAMBERS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18450512-name-1071" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES CHAMBERS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City police-constable, No.</hi> 523.) I was on duty in Lime-street at half-past five o'clock on the morning of the 18th of April—I saw the prisoner in company with another man—I saw the pri<lb></lb>soner had a coat on which was too large for him—the other man ran away—I went and took the prisoner—I asked him where he got that coat—he said he bought it four or five months ago in Petticoat-lane—I took him to the station—the inspector found this letter in the pocket of the coat—this is the coat he had on.</p>
